  "time_ut": 1656500321,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0db4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dbd\u0dcf-\u0dc4\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0da0\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca \u0dad\u0dd3\u0dbb\u0dab \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dad\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dbb\u0da7\u0dda \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0db3\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The problems of the country cannot be solved until the Rajapaksa-henchmen take decisions",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa and other parties responsible for the current crisis in the country should go home now, said the Leader of the 43 Division, Parliamentarian Patali Champika Ranawaka today (29).",
        "As long as the Rajapaksas are in power and the Rajapaksas and their henchmen make key decisions in the regime and as long as the Petroleum Corporation and the CEB run the institutions, there will be no confidence in the country internationally or locally, he said.",
        "Therefore, the President should resign immediately without causing bloodshed in the country, he said, adding that the issue should be exacerbated and the country should not be bloodied.",
        "Mr. Ranawaka said Sri Lanka owed $ 1,000 million in sovereign bonds on the 25th of next month and that a $ 250 million company had already filed a lawsuit against Sri Lanka, but said it had no confidence in Sri Lanka's support from the International Monetary Fund over the impact of the case.",
        "Mr. Patali Champika Ranawaka stated this addressing a media briefing held at the 43 Division Office, Narahenpita.",
        "He said that the Rajapaksa family members should stop interfering in the importation of oil and gas."
      ],
